// Contracts demo: capabilities catch dangerous code, contracts catch wrong code.
//
// `max` is pure — no capabilities, nothing dangerous — it just returns the
// wrong answer. Its `ensures` clauses pin down what "the maximum" means: the
// result must be at least each input. This body returns the difference instead,
// so the postcondition is violated and the implementation is blamed.
fn max(a: Int, b: Int) -> Int
    ensures result >= a
    ensures result >= b
{
    return a - b;
}
